Here's how to do it using `Window` lifecycle events and `Preferences`:

**1. Create a custom `Window` subclass:**

```csharp
// AppWindow.cs
public class AppWindow : Window
{
    private NoteViewModel? _viewModel;

    public AppWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }

    public void SetViewModel(NoteViewModel vm) => _viewModel = vm;

    protected override void OnStopped()
    {
        base.OnStopped();
        if (_viewModel is not null)
            Preferences.Set("draft_text", _viewModel.DraftText);
    }

    protected override void OnResumed()
    {
        base.OnResumed();
        if (_viewModel is not null)
            _viewModel.DraftText = Preferences.Get("draft_text", string.Empty);
    }

    protected override void OnDestroying()
    {
        base.OnDestroying();
        // Android back-button can skip Stopped entirely
        if (_viewModel is not null)
            Preferences.Set("draft_text", _viewModel.DraftText);
    }
}
```

**2. Return it from `App.CreateWindow`:**

```csharp
// App.xaml.cs
public partial class App : Application
{
    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
        => new AppWindow(new AppShell());
}
```

**3. Register the view model from your page:**

```csharp
// NotePage.xaml.cs
protected override void OnAppearing()
{
    base.OnAppearing();
    if (Window is AppWindow appWindow)
        appWindow.SetViewModel((NoteViewModel)BindingContext);
}
```

### Key things to know

| Concern | Guidance |
|---|---|
| **`Resumed` doesn't fire on first launch** | Initial sequence is `Created` → `Activated`. Load any saved draft in your page's `OnAppearing` or constructor instead. |
| **Android back button** | Can call `Destroying` without `Stopped`, so save in **both** `OnStopped` and `OnDestroying`. |
| **Keep handlers fast** | `Preferences` is ideal — avoid database writes here. Android enforces a ~5s ANR timeout; iOS has a similar watchdog. |
| **`Deactivated` ≠ `Stopped`** | A notification shade pull-down fires `Deactivated` but the app isn't backgrounded. Don't save there — wait for `Stopped`. |
